d more for being the most self-less giving person I've ever had the fortune of being guilded with.<br><br>In short, most of the people in our guild who have a &quot;guild&quot; item probably already know what they SHOULD give back if they left; and I hope we've chosen people with the character and backbone TO give them back.  (Because in all honesty, we can't make them...)<br><br>If Tides of Valor deserved the CoF, then you should have given it back.  If you deserved the CoF, then you should have kept it (if you didn't have an agreement beforehand).  And remember, not every agreement is spoken.  If you saw 10 other people get an item and then pass it along or give it up when asked, you can expect the same sort of tacit agreement to bind your behavior too.<br><br>People have left Vision on good terms.  People have left Vision on bad terms.  The number one distinction for seperating the two are generally the people who told us the truth are on the &quot;good terms&quot; list.  Some people just don't &quot;fit&quot; into a guild.  Look at your real circle of friends and co-workers.  That guy you work with, who you don't have lunch with, he's probably not a bad guy, he's probably just not YOUR TYPE of guy.<br><br><!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> This morning... A necro in tides of valor Asks me if he can Dupe the cloak of flame i had gotten in tides before the patch... I mean jeez... im a troll but im not that stupid.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>*grumble* <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4868>Palimax Sceleris</a>,Guildleader: <a href=http://www.guildvision.org>Vision</a>, Grandmaster <a href=http://www.base-nine.org/available_tinkering_items.htm>Tinkerer</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/utremainbladesinger.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TremainBladesinger</A></span><br> <span class=use